create a spatial scatter plot for the data
Predicted API: squidpy.pl.spatial_scatter

The task is to create a spatial scatter plot for a given data set, overlaying other data on top and having the option to plot background images. We solved it by employing the function squidpy.pl.spatial_scatter from the Squidpy package, which allows granular control over visualization via various parameters such as the scale of the shapes plotted, image display settings, coordinate space cropping, color customization, and more. This function defaults to a scatter plot if no image is plotted and handles multiple datasets, which means it can plot all unique libraries sequentially or select specific libraries.
